<!-- CONCEPTS -->
<section id="concepts">
<div class="container">
  <p class="section-label reveal">Core Concepts</p>
  <h2 class="section-title reveal">What You'll Learn</h2>
  <p class="section-sub reveal">From the basics of TCP/IP to building real WLAN applications — everything covered step by step.</p>

  <div class="concepts-grid">
    <div class="concept-card reveal" style="--accent:var(--c4);">
      <span class="concept-icon" style="animation-delay:.0s">📡</span>
      <h3>What is a Socket?</h3>
      <p>A socket is an endpoint in a network communication — like a power outlet for data. Every connected program needs one to send or receive.</p>
      <span class="tag" style="--accent:var(--c4)">Foundation</span>
    </div>
    <div class="concept-card reveal" style="--accent:var(--c2);">
      <span class="concept-icon" style="animation-delay:.2s">🔗</span>
      <h3>TCP vs UDP</h3>
      <p>TCP guarantees delivery and order — like certified mail. UDP is fast but unreliable — like shouting across a room. Use TCP for chat, UDP for gaming.</p>
      <span class="tag" style="--accent:var(--c2)">Transport Layer</span>
    </div>
    <div class="concept-card reveal" style="--accent:var(--c3);">
      <span class="concept-icon" style="animation-delay:.4s">🏠</span>
      <h3>IP Addresses on WLAN</h3>
      <p>Devices on the same Wi-Fi share a network (e.g. 192.168.1.x). The client uses the server's LAN IP — not localhost — to connect over Wi-Fi.</p>
      <span class="tag" style="--accent:var(--c3)">Networking</span>
    </div>
    <div class="concept-card reveal" style="--accent:var(--c5);">
      <span class="concept-icon" style="animation-delay:.6s">🤝</span>
      <h3>TCP 3-Way Handshake</h3>
      <p>Before data flows, TCP establishes trust: SYN → SYN-ACK → ACK. This happens automatically when you call connect() in C.</p>
      <span class="tag" style="--accent:var(--c5)">Protocol</span>
    </div>
    <div class="concept-card reveal" style="--accent:var(--c1);">
      <span class="concept-icon" style="animation-delay:.8s">🔢</span>
      <h3>Byte Order (Endianness)</h3>
      <p>Networks use big-endian format. Always convert ports with htons() and IPs with inet_pton() — or your packets won't be understood.</p>
      <span class="tag" style="--accent:var(--c1)">Low Level</span>
    </div>
    <div class="concept-card reveal" style="--accent:var(--c7);">
      <span class="concept-icon" style="animation-delay:1s">⚡</span>
      <h3>send() &amp; recv() Loop</h3>
      <p>Data exchange happens in a loop — send messages, receive replies. Neither call guarantees all bytes in one shot; always check the return value!</p>
      <span class="tag" style="--accent:var(--c7)">Core API</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

